        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-01-18T17:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-01-18T17:16:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <head>449. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d449fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 303, Agency Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Vol. X. Secret; Exdis.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1972-01-18T22:16:00+00:00">January 18, 1972,
                        2216Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Subj: <gloss target="#t_PRC1">PRC</gloss>’s Interest in Senior Secretariat
                    Post.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>During talk with me Jan 14, <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>, among
                        other things, told me he had recently discussed <gloss target="#t_PRC1"
                            >PRC</gloss> position in Secretariat with <persName corresp="#p_HH1"
                            >Huang Hua</persName>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>When <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Huang Hua</persName> recently called on
                            <persName corresp="#p_WK1">Waldheim</persName> to discuss Chinese
                        interest in a top Secretariat position, he asked <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                            >SYG</gloss> what suggestions he had concerning an appropriate position.
                            <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> proposed the <persName
                            corresp="#p_DI1">Djermakoye</persName> job (Under <gloss
                            target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> for Trusteeship and Non-Self-Governing
                        Territories). <persName corresp="#p_WK1">Waldheim</persName> said that
                            <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Huang Hua</persName> listened politely but
                        then made clear this would be unacceptable. The <gloss target="#t_PRC1"
                            >PRC</gloss>, <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Huang Hua</persName> said, was
                        interested in a senior political position. First he mentioned the Under
                            <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> for Political and Security Affairs
                        (occupied by <persName corresp="#p_KLN1">Kutakovy</persName>). When
                            <persName corresp="#p_WK1">Waldheim</persName> pointed out the
                        impossibility of dislodging the Soviet incumbent, <persName corresp="#p_HH1"
                            >Huang Hua</persName> suggested the position of Chef de Cabinet as an
                        alternative.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Huang Hua</persName> felt that the Indians were
                        too strongly entrenched in the Secretariat and that <persName
                            corresp="#p_NCV1">Narasimhan</persName> should be replaced.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WK1">Waldheim</persName> made no commitments but told
                        him that he would take into account the Chinese desire for a top level
                        political position.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PCH1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
